President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Oklahoma due to severe winter storms that occurred from February 8 to February 20, 2021. This declaration allows for federal funding to assist individuals, businesses, and local governments in the affected areas. Assistance can include grants for housing and repairs, loans for property losses, and other recovery programs. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Adam D. Burpee as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.